Amabutho (Zulu regiments) wielded spears, shields and clubs known as "knobkerries" JOHANNESBURG - Eskom says there will be no load-shedding during AmaZulu King Goodwill Zwelithini's memorial service. The utility increased rolling power cuts to stage two on Wednesday night but the whole country will have power between 10am and 2pm on Thursday in order to witness the historically significant memorial. READ: South Africans mourn longest-serving AmaZulu monarch From Thursday afternoon though, stage two load-shedding will kick in again and continue until 5am on Saturday. Eskom says it's lost generating capacity at a number of its power stations and is experiencing an increase in demand.